/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/btc20_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/merge_stdout.log:1:{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Upgradeable presale exposes no initializer, leaving proxy owner and all core configuration permanently unset","locations":["0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:31","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:78","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/access/OwnableUpgradeable.sol:29","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/security/PausableUpgradeable.sol:34","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/security/ReentrancyGuardUpgradeable.sol:40"],"claim":"PresaleV5 inherits Initializable, OwnableUpgradeable, PausableUpgradeable, and ReentrancyGuardUpgradeable, but the contract defines no external initializer that calls __Ownable_init, __Pausable_init, __ReentrancyGuard_init, or sets required sale configuration. The constructor only consumes the initializer slot on the implementation, so a proxy instance starts with owner == address(0) and every configurable dependency/value left at its zero default.","impact":"All onlyOwner administration paths are permanently unreachable on the proxy, so the sale cannot be configured, paused, funded for claims, or repaired through this implementation. Any assets later routed into the proxy can become stuck behind an ownerless contract until the proxy admin deploys and upgrades to a different implementation.","paths":["Deploy PresaleV5 behind a proxy","Observe that no external initialize/reinitialize function exists to set owner or core parameters","Any call guarded by onlyOwner reverts forever because owner() remains address(0)"] ,"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Claim functions ignore claimStart and allow early withdrawals or staking","locations":["0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:130","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:151","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:164","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:181"],"claim":"Although startClaim stores claimStart and changeClaimStart lets the owner move it, neither claim() nor claimAndStake() checks block.timestamp against claimStart before releasing a user's allocation.","impact":"Once startClaim has funded the contract and enabled claiming, eligible users can bypass the intended vesting or TGE delay and pull or stake their full allocation immediately. That breaks launch scheduling and can enable premature dumping or reward extraction ahead of the advertised claim date.","paths":["Owner calls startClaim with a future claimStart","User is eligible to claim or claim-and-stake","User calls claim() or claimAndStake() before claimStart and still receives the allocation flow immediately"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Claim funding check is ineffective because totalTokensSold is never updated","locations":["0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:32","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:130","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:131","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:273","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:292","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:307","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:320","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:336"],"claim":"startClaim() tries to ensure the contract receives enough claim tokens by requiring noOfTokens >= totalTokensSold * baseDecimals, but totalTokensSold is never incremented anywhere in the contract. User balances can still be created through updateFromBSC(), while the active sale paths increment a different variable, directTotalTokensSold.","impact":"The contract can enter the claim phase with far fewer tokens than users are owed. Early claimants can drain the funded balance and later claimants will revert on transfer, leaving purchased allocations permanently underfunded or locked.","paths":["Owner imports claim balances through updateFromBSC(), increasing userDeposits","totalTokensSold remains zero because no code path updates it","Owner calls startClaim with too few sale tokens and the check still passes","Some users claim successfully until the contract balance is exhausted, after which later claimants cannot receive their tokens"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"USDT purchase paths treat any non-reverting low-level call as successful payment","locations":["0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:304","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:310","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:333","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:339"],"claim":"buyWithUSDT() and buyWithUSDTDynamic() perform a raw low-level call to transferFrom and only check the CALL opcode success flag. They never decode the returned bool and never verify that USDTInterface actually points to a token contract.","impact":"If the configured payment token returns false instead of reverting, or if the payment token address is misconfigured to an EOA or other non-token target, the functions still continue and allocate stake or transfer sale tokens without receiving payment. That can distribute inventory for free and leave the sale undercollateralized.","paths":["USDTInterface is set to a token that returns false on failed transferFrom, or to an address with no code","Buyer calls buyWithUSDT() or buyWithUSDTDynamic() without a real payment succeeding","The low-level call returns success == true, so the contract proceeds to credit the purchase anyway"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Staking manager address is never validated, so purchase and claim-and-stake flows can succeed while recording no stake","locations":["0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:139","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:191","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:284","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:285","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:297","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:312"],"claim":"The contract blindly casts any supplied address to StakingManager in both startClaim() and setStakingManager(), then assumes depositByPresale() created a real stake. There is no zero-address check, code-size check, interface check, or post-condition verifying that a stake was actually recorded.","impact":"If the staking manager is misconfigured to address(0), an EOA, or an incompatible contract, buyWithEth(), buyWithUSDT(), and claimAndStake() can complete while creating no stake position. Users can therefore pay funds or burn their stored claim balance yet receive nothing on the staking side.","paths":["Owner/configuration sets staking manager to an EOA, zero address, or incompatible contract","User calls buyWithEth(), buyWithUSDT(), or claimAndStake()","The external call does not establish a real stake, but the presale flow still proceeds and the user's funds or claim balance are consumed"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Configured sale window is dead code because none of the buy functions enforce startTime or endTime","locations":["0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:118","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:289","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:304","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:317","0xe69be7d6b306b4fbce516e3f07c8f438a6860084/contracts/ETH/PresaleV5.sol:333"],"claim":"The contract defines checkSaleState() to enforce block.timestamp within startTime/endTime, but none of the four purchase functions use that modifier or replicate its checks. Purchases are gated only by whenNotPaused, dynamicSaleState, and maxTokensToSell.","impact":"Whenever dynamicSaleState is enabled, users can buy before the intended opening time or after the intended closing time. This breaks the advertised sale schedule and can enable unauthorized late or early participation.","paths":["Owner sets a sale window via startTime and endTime","dynamicSaleState remains enabled outside that window","Buyer calls any buy function before startTime or after endTime","Purchase succeeds because no buy path checks the configured time bounds"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Missing nonReentrant modifier on USDT buy functions","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The concrete risk here is the unsafe low-level USDT payment handling itself; a separate reentrancy finding was not substantiated beyond the same misconfigured/malicious-token assumption and did not show an additional protocol-harm path."},{"title":"Owner can change staking contract to any address","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"As stated, this is an owner-privilege observation rather than an independent vulnerability. The reportable issue is the lack of validation that allows accidental misconfiguration to silently break staking flows, which is already captured in F-005."},{"title":"Unlimited token approval in startClaim without revocation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Changing stakingContract later does not grant the new address the old approval; the approval remains with the address approved in startClaim. The candidate's drain path is incorrect as written and reduces to trusted-admin risk."},{"title":"Division before multiplication causes precision loss","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The ETH path already multiplies before dividing, and the USDT path's decimal conversion only introduces normal rounding/truncation. No realistic fund-loss or exploitable protocol-level harm was supported."},{"title":"claimAndStake deletes userDeposits before verifying staking success","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"If depositByPresale reverts, the whole transaction reverts and userDeposits is not deleted. The real issue is silent success against an invalid staking target, which is covered by F-005."},{"title":"No slippage protection on token purchases","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is a fixed-price sale flow, not an AMM swap. The absence of a min-out parameter is not a standalone vulnerability on the shown code paths."},{"title":"Missing events for critical administrative functions","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is observability/code-quality feedback, not a realistic protocol-harm issue."},{"title":"No access control on updateFromBSC function","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The function is gated by onlyOwner. Arbitrary owner-controlled imports are a trust/centralization property, not a missing-access-control bug."},{"title":"stakeingWhitelistStatus can be disabled after claims start","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is an owner-controlled policy toggle with no unsupported access path. It does not constitute an independent vulnerability."}]}
